<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="795" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1660</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-25"><hi rend="italic">April 25,
                                        1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April
                                        26, 2 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1944. Swedish press reports from Moscow Foreign Commissariat has sent
                                following telegram to German Foreign Ministry: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>We learn that German-Ukrainian troops have crossed Perekop
                                        and advanced on Simferopol despite declaration of
                                        German-Ukrainian Government that does not belong to
                                        territory Ukrainian republic. Advancing of German-Ukrainian
                                        troops in Crimea constitutes violation of Brest treaty. This
                                        raid being threat to our Black Sea Fleet, [measures] will
                                        have to be taken for its security which might lead to
                                        deplorable events. Commissariat in expressing hopes that
                                        troops in Crimea will be ordered to retire requests German
                                        Government immediately to notify us that request been
                                        complied with.</p></quote></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_MIN1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>